{
  "texts": [
    "Their primary goals may be less intrinsically motivated but eventually correspond rather to the mere accomplishment of educational tasks like the submission of seminar papers, homework, or sample calculations.",
    "In light of the especially low opportunity costs of LLMs, supporting a playful approach for working with them also under those circumstances may require more than to appeal to individual integrity and virtue.",
    "Such support, however, may then be accomplished by providing a learning environment in which playing becomes a natural form of activity (Plass et al., 2020) and a designed pathway to learning.",
    "That means, such support may be provided by a pedagogy of learning based on games.",
    "Games, in both non-digital and digital forms, have repeatedly proven valuable for learning, training, and education (Dillon et al., 2017; Pahor et al., 2022; Pasqualotto et al., 2022)."
  ]
}